Heavy rains could disrupt Coast BBI rally             Sigomba Ramadhan Omar  24th Jan 2020 12:12:12 GMT +0300 Sigomba Ramadhan Omar  24th Jan 2020 12:12:12 GMT +0300 Sigomba Ramadhan Omar   Most of the roads in Mombasa become impassable following heavy rains. The Meteorological Department has issued a heavy rain alert in Mombasa over the weekend when the BBI rally is expected to take place at Tononoka Grounds. [File, Standard]  Most of the roads in Mombasa become impassable following heavy rains. The Meteorological Department has issued a heavy rain alert in Mombasa over the weekend when the BBI rally is expected to take place at Tononoka Grounds. [File, Standard] Most of the roads in Mombasa become impassable following heavy rains. The Meteorological Department has issued a heavy rain alert in Mombasa over the weekend when the BBI rally is expected to take place at Tononoka Grounds. [File, Standard] Most of the roads in Mombasa become impassable following heavy rains. The Meteorological Department has issued a heavy rain alert in Mombasa over the weekend when the BBI rally is expected to take place at Tononoka Grounds. It might be a wet Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) rally in Mombasa after the weatherman predicted heavy rainfall at the coast region over the weekend.          SEE ALSO :Unforgiving rivers return to reclaim grabbed pathways SEE ALSO : Unforgiving rivers return to reclaim grabbed pathways    For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Subscribe Now » Subscribe Now »       SEE ALSO :Poor road conditions leave motorists stranded in Samburu SEE ALSO : Poor road conditions leave motorists stranded in Samburu      SEE ALSO :3,000 displaced by floods SEE ALSO : 3,000 displaced by floods Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Di